  • Method Details

    • assignableFrom

      boolean assignableFrom(ExternType other)
      Return whether this type is assignable from (is a supertype of) the other, by import subtyping.

      This formally returns this >= other, for the subtyping relation >=.

      Parameters:
      other - The other type.
      Returns:
      Whether this type matches (is a supertype of) other.

    • intersection

      @Nullable @Nullable ExternType intersection(ExternType other)
      Returns the most general type which is the subtype of both this and the other, or null (representing the bottom type) if no such actual type exists.

      The result of this is guaranteed to be such that this and other are both assignableFrom(ExternType) the result.

      Formally, this is the greatest lower bound (infimum) of the subtyping relation.

      Parameters:
      other - The other type.
      Returns:
      The most general type assignable to both this and other.

    • getLocal

      static ExternType getLocal(ModuleNode module, ExternType.Kind kind, int index)
      Get the type of the indexth local entity (func, global, memory, table) in the WebAssembly module.

      The index here does not refer to the usual WebAssembly indices, which include imports. This excludes imports, and only considers the local entities. Use fromImport(AbstractImportNode, ModuleNode) for imported types.

      Parameters:
      module - The module.
      kind - The kind of entity.
      index - The index of the entity.
      Returns:
      The type of the entity.
